examples.en: Hi there, you must be Laura.
Don't cry, Laura. It'll be OK.
Laura is very mature for her age.
Laura gazed absently out of the window.
Deep in his heart, he wanted Laura back.
Laura's sat six exams and has two more to go.
Laura could hardly wait to see the twins again.
Laura left her native England to live in France.
Tim had miscalculated: Laura would never disobey her father.
'He's nice,' said Laura, crossing her fingers under the table.
As she grew older, Laura became increasingly disillusioned with politics.
Diana and Laura have been firm friends (=close friends) since their early teens.
The cloth had a natural look which coincided perfectly with the image Laura sought.
Laura praised the pictures, though she privately thought they were rather ordinary.
Careful, Laura. You could be treading on dangerous ground (=expressing opinions etc that might offend someone).
